<br>
I have never used kthx or any of those though occasionally you will see my pop off a wtf. Hehe if you are a caster you know the feeling when you are just about done waiting for your power to regen just to have an assassin come and one shot you. So most of the time you see me say that I just got one shotted. I know some believe to say inc is bad and fortunatly i rarely have to say that word as a caster. Usually i am doing the Indiana Jones run from the rolling rock with a bunch of albs behind me and i am trying to warn all my fellow hibs <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  But i dont see anything wrong with using the word. I have always understood it to be a pullers quick way to say incoming. As a monk in EQ i know what its like to run with a mob on you.<br>
<br>
I must say I never realized the degree roleplaying was taken to and at first i was more in shock. I still believe certain levels should be tolerated and understood a little more as long as there is some RPing involved. But i do enjoy those who take RP to that higher level a lot more then the ones who just like to get the job done. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#110d03><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub49.ezboard.com/uailaen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ailaen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Hibernian Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#006400>(3/19/02 6:05:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub49.ezboard.com/fhiberniaonguiniverefrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lack of actual Roleplaying on our server</span><hr size=1> For me, roleplaying in a game like this is dependant on context. If I'm in a hunting group, I'm more of a casual roleplayer. I'm still playing my character, still responding to events as my character would, but the emphasis is less on roleplay and more on hunting or what have you.<br>
<br>
At a roleplay event, on the other hand, I step it up a notch and try to come up with stories for my character, his heritage, history, personality, etc. I think there's room for both.<br>
<br>
Really, I've found that the first rule of roleplay is not to break someone else's immersion. I try not to /broadcast stats in Tir na Nog, because that always annoys someone, I try not to talk about my OOC spec strategies in a group. If it's clear that the people you're hanging out with don't mind a mix of the two, then that's fine, but I think as long as you're not annoying someone else on an RP server with your obvious non-RP, there's not a lot to worry about.<br>
